Package space.sunqian.fs.di

Interface DIContainer

public interface DIContainer
This interface represents a DI container that manages the injection of dependencies into objects.

A DI container is typically created via newBuilder(), which is used to configure the container's components and behaviors. See DI documentation for more information.

    • initialize

      DIContainer initialize() throws DIInitializeException, DIException
      Initializes this DI container.

      All post-construct methods of this DI container's components are executed sequentially according to their dependency relationships. If an exception occurs during the execution, an DIInitializeException will be thrown and the initialization process will terminate immediately, successfully initialized components will not be rolled back and the uninitialized components will not be initialized. See DI documentation for more information. A DI container can only initialize once and cannot re-initialize.

      This method blocks current thread until the initialization operation is completed.

      Returns:
      this DI container
      Throws:
      DIInitializeException - if any post-construct method execution fails
      DIException - if any other error occurs during initialization operation

    • isInitialized

      boolean isInitialized()
      Returns whether this DI container is initialized.
      Returns:
      true if this DI container is initialized; false otherwise

    • shutdown

      DIContainer shutdown() throws DIShutdownException, DIException
      Shuts down this DI container.

      All pre-destroy methods of this DI container's components are executed sequentially according to their dependency relationships. If an exception occurs during the execution, an DIShutdownException will be thrown and the shutdown process will terminate immediately, successfully destroyed components will not be rolled back and the un-destroyed components will not be destroyed. See DI documentation for more information. A DI container can only shut down once and cannot re-shutdown.

      Sub-containers are not automatically shut down along with this container, but components that sub-containers depend on from this DI container will be destroyed by this DI container.

      This method blocks current thread until the shutdown operation is completed.

      Returns:
      this DI container
      Throws:
      DIShutdownException - if any pre-destroy method execution fails
      DIException - if any other error occurs during shutdown operation

    • getComponent

      @Nullable @Nullable DIComponent getComponent(@Nonnull @Nonnull Type type)
      Returns the component whose type is assignable to the specified type, or null if no such component exists.

      This method first attempts to find a component whose type exactly matches the specified type using Object.equals(Object). If no exact match is found, it will randomly select one component that can be assigned to the specified type from all components that constitute this container.

      Parameters:
      type - the specified type
      Returns:
      the component whose type is assignable to the specified type, or null if no such component exists
